{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"When I was 27 years old,"},{"time":2954,"text":"I left a very demanding job\nin management consulting"},{"time":6301,"text":"for a job that was even more\ndemanding: teaching."},{"time":11298,"text":"I went to teach seventh graders math"},{"time":13802,"text":"in the New York City public schools."},{"time":16202,"text":"And like any teacher,\nI made quizzes and tests."},{"time":19107,"text":"I gave out homework assignments."},{"time":21107,"text":"When the work came back,\nI calculated grades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24758,"text":"What struck me was that IQ\nwas not the only difference"},{"time":29334,"text":"between my best and my worst students."},{"time":33017,"text":"Some of my strongest performers\ndid not have stratospheric IQ scores."},{"time":38345,"text":"Some of my smartest kids\nweren't doing so well."},{"time":42297,"text":"And that got me thinking."},{"time":44432,"text":"The kinds of things you need\nto learn in seventh grade math,"},{"time":47416,"text":"sure, they're hard: ratios, decimals,\nthe area of a parallelogram."},{"time":52668,"text":"But these concepts are not impossible,"},{"time":55368,"text":"and I was firmly convinced\nthat every one of my students"},{"time":59502,"text":"could learn the material"},{"time":62106,"text":"if they worked hard and long enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64842,"text":"After several more years of teaching,"},{"time":67328,"text":"I came to the conclusion\nthat what we need in education"},{"time":71086,"text":"is a much better understanding\nof students and learning"},{"time":74570,"text":"from a motivational perspective,"},{"time":76911,"text":"from a psychological perspective."},{"time":79815,"text":"In education, the one thing\nwe know how to measure best is IQ."},{"time":86172,"text":"But what if doing\nwell in school and in life"},{"time":90048,"text":"depends on much more"},{"time":92166,"text":"than your ability to learn\nquickly and easily?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96371,"text":"So I left the classroom,"},{"time":98321,"text":"and I went to graduate school\nto become a psychologist."},{"time":101877,"text":"I started studying kids and adults"},{"time":104051,"text":"in all kinds of super\nchallenging settings,"},{"time":106908,"text":"and in every study my question was,"},{"time":109360,"text":"who is successful here and why?"},{"time":112384,"text":"My research team and I went\nto West Point Military Academy."},{"time":116476,"text":"We tried to predict which cadets"},{"time":118160,"text":"would stay in military training\nand which would drop out."},{"time":122414,"text":"We went to the National Spelling Bee"},{"time":124669,"text":"and tried to predict which children\nwould advance farthest in competition."},{"time":129867,"text":"We studied rookie teachers\nworking in really tough neighborhoods,"},{"time":133947,"text":"asking which teachers are still\ngoing to be here in teaching"},{"time":137388,"text":"by the end of the school year,"},{"time":139406,"text":"and of those, who will be\nthe most effective"},{"time":142441,"text":"at improving learning\noutcomes for their students?"},{"time":145592,"text":"We partnered with private\ncompanies, asking,"},{"time":147846,"text":"which of these salespeople\nis going to keep their jobs?"},{"time":150565,"text":"And who's going to earn the most money?"},{"time":152797,"text":"In all those very different contexts,"},{"time":155479,"text":"one characteristic emerged\nas a significant predictor of success."},{"time":160464,"text":"And it wasn't social intelligence."},{"time":162662,"text":"It wasn't good looks, physical health,"},{"time":165671,"text":"and it wasn't IQ."},{"time":167758,"text":"It was grit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169899,"text":"Grit is passion and perseverance\nfor very long-term goals."},{"time":174989,"text":"Grit is having stamina."},{"time":177232,"text":"Grit is sticking with your future,\nday in, day out,"},{"time":181462,"text":"not just for the week,\nnot just for the month,"},{"time":184851,"text":"but for years,"},{"time":186407,"text":"and working really hard\nto make that future a reality."},{"time":190969,"text":"Grit is living life\nlike it's a marathon, not a sprint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196156,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":197611,"text":"I started studying grit\nin the Chicago public schools."},{"time":201141,"text":"I asked thousands of high school juniors"},{"time":203453,"text":"to take grit questionnaires,"},{"time":205305,"text":"and then waited around more than a year"},{"time":207281,"text":"to see who would graduate."},{"time":209518,"text":"Turns out that grittier kids"},{"time":211764,"text":"were significantly more\nlikely to graduate,"},{"time":214968,"text":"even when I matched them\non every characteristic I could measure,"},{"time":218754,"text":"things like family income,"},{"time":221028,"text":"standardized achievement test scores,"},{"time":223774,"text":"even how safe kids felt\nwhen they were at school."},{"time":227377,"text":"So it's not just at West Point\nor the National Spelling Bee"},{"time":230338,"text":"that grit matters."},{"time":231476,"text":"It's also in school,"},{"time":233441,"text":"especially for kids\nat risk for dropping out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237116,"text":"To me, the most shocking thing about grit"},{"time":240098,"text":"is how little we know,"},{"time":242081,"text":"how little science knows,\nabout building it."},{"time":245003,"text":"Every day, parents and teachers ask me,"},{"time":247278,"text":"\"How do I build grit in kids?"},{"time":249502,"text":"What do I do to teach kids\na solid work ethic?"},{"time":252753,"text":"How do I keep them motivated\nfor the long run?\""},{"time":255860,"text":"The honest answer is,"},{"time":257859,"text":"I don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260459,"text":"What I do know is that talent\ndoesn't make you gritty."},{"time":263522,"text":"Our data show very clearly"},{"time":265877,"text":"that there are many talented individuals"},{"time":268314,"text":"who simply do not follow through\non their commitments."},{"time":271814,"text":"In fact, in our data,\ngrit is usually unrelated"},{"time":276052,"text":"or even inversely related\nto measures of talent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280465,"text":"So far, the best idea I've heard\nabout building grit in kids"},{"time":284584,"text":"is something called \"growth mindset.\""},{"time":287449,"text":"This is an idea developed\nat Stanford University by Carol Dweck,"},{"time":291143,"text":"and it is the belief that the ability\nto learn is not fixed,"},{"time":296265,"text":"that it can change with your effort."},{"time":299440,"text":"Dr. Dweck has shown"},{"time":300783,"text":"that when kids read\nand learn about the brain"},{"time":303942,"text":"and how it changes and grows\nin response to challenge,"},{"time":307440,"text":"they're much more likely\nto persevere when they fail,"},{"time":311461,"text":"because they don't believe that failure\nis a permanent condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317052,"text":"So growth mindset\nis a great idea for building grit."},{"time":320724,"text":"But we need more."},{"time":322825,"text":"And that's where I'm going\nto end my remarks,"},{"time":324945,"text":"because that's where we are."},{"time":326315,"text":"That's the work that stands before us."},{"time":328504,"text":"We need to take our best ideas,\nour strongest intuitions,"},{"time":332408,"text":"and we need to test them."},{"time":334512,"text":"We need to measure\nwhether we've been successful,"},{"time":337247,"text":"and we have to be willing\nto fail, to be wrong,"},{"time":340977,"text":"to start over again with lessons learned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344336,"text":"In other words, we need to be gritty"},{"time":347304,"text":"about getting our kids grittier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350177,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351233,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}